description:
AVAILABILITY:
At any point on Company's existing secondary distribution lines of adequate capacity and suitable voltage.


APPLICABLE: 

To all electric service for the customer's equipment used in pumping and aeration of catfish ponds and/or used in farm irrigation pumping, where the customer has volunteered and been accepted by the Company to participate in the test project in which this rate shall be applied. (See the section below entitled "Test Period and Contract Periods.") Such service will be supplied at one point of delivery and measured through one kilowatt-hour meter. 

Not applicable for resale or shared service.

 TEST PERIOD AND CONTRACT PERIODS

The test period for this Rate Schedule shall not terminate before December 31, 1989. The
Contract Period for customers contracting for service under this Rate Schedule shall be for a
minimum of one year (twelve billing periods) or until the termination of this Rate Schedule (not
before January 1, 1990), whichever is earlier.
